    • Enum Constant Detail

      • MANHATTAN

        public static final DijkstraMap.Measurement MANHATTAN
        The distance it takes when only the four primary directions can be moved in. The default.

      • CHEBYSHEV

        public static final DijkstraMap.Measurement CHEBYSHEV
        The distance it takes when diagonal movement costs the same as cardinal movement.

      • EUCLIDEAN

        public static final DijkstraMap.Measurement EUCLIDEAN
        The distance it takes as the crow flies. This will NOT affect movement cost when calculating a path, only the preferred squares to travel to (resulting in drastically more reasonable-looking paths).

      • matchingMeasurement

        public static DijkstraMap.Measurement matchingMeasurement(Radius radius)
        Gets the appropriate DijkstraMap.Measurement that matches a Radius enum. Matches SQUARE or CUBE to CHEBYSHEV, DIAMOND or OCTAHEDRON to MANHATTAN, and CIRCLE or SPHERE to EUCLIDEAN.
        Equivalent to DijkstraMap.findMeasurement(Radius).
        Parameters:
        radius - the Radius to find the corresponding Measurement for
        Returns:
        a DijkstraMap.Measurement that matches radius; SQUARE to CHEBYSHEV, DIAMOND to MANHATTAN, etc.

      • matchingRadius

        public Radius matchingRadius()
        Gets the appropriate Radius corresponding to a DijkstraMap.Measurement. Matches CHEBYSHEV to SQUARE, MANHATTAN to DIAMOND, and EUCLIDEAN to CIRCLE.
        You may also consider DijkstraMap.findRadius(Measurement), which is a static method with the same general capability.
        Returns:
        a Radius enum that matches this Measurement; CHEBYSHEV to SQUARE, MANHATTAN to DIAMOND, etc.
